article.headline: Texas-Pan American 92, Eureka 64
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Justin Leathers scored 14 points, leading four players in double figures, to help Texas-Pan American beat Eureka 92-64 on Thursday night. Jesus Delgado scored 13, and Aaron Urbanus had 11 points and seven assists for the Broncos (3-7). Brandon Provost had 12 points and nine rebounds. Texas Pan-American led 49-39 at halftime and outrebounded the Red Devils 46-25. The Broncos shot 56 percent from the field, while Eureka shot 44 percent. Mark Lessen led Eureka with 17 points and eight rebounds. D. T. Thornton had 13 points and Jordan Fehr had 11. Eureka (3-5) plays in the NAIA. The game was the first meeting between the two teams.
